# Task: Implement Advanced Time Tracking System

**Created:** 2025-11-22
**Status:** Planning
**Priority:** P1 (High - Core Feature Gap)
**Complexity:** High
**Estimated Effort:** 6-8 weeks (phased)

---

## Context

Neuman Brain currently has **23% Toggl parity** for time tracking (see `docs/product/feature_map.md:769-806`). This is our biggest feature gap. We have:
- ✅ Time tracking database (`src/db/timeTrackingDb.ts`)
- ✅ Basic timer service in Kanban store (start/stop/pause)
- ✅ Pomodoro widget (`src/widgets/Dashboard/PomodoroWidget.tsx`)
- ❌ No manual time entry UI
- ❌ No reporting/analytics
- ❌ No timer widget on dashboard
- ❌ No time entry editing
- ❌ No invoicing/billing features

**Research completed:** Analyzed Toggl, Clockify, ActivityWatch, Rize, Timely, RescueTime, and developer-focused tools (WakaTime, Taskwarrior+Timewarrior, Linear, Super Productivity).

**Goal:** Achieve **85-90% parity** with Toggl Track while maintaining Neuman Brain's privacy-first, widget-based architecture.

